<h2>Prusa Mesh Leveling</h2>
<form class="form-horizontal">
    <h3>GCODE Script</h3>
    <p>
    Specify the GCODE script to perform the mesh bed level operation as well as to check its status after the leveling operation completes. You may also include your own stuff here, like bed temps or PINDA temperature stabilization. Just make sure your extras happen before G81.
    </p>
    <div class="control-group">
        <label class="control-label">Mesh Leveling GCode Script</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <textarea rows="4" class="block" data-bind="value: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.PrusaMeshMap.do_level_gcode"></textarea>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Heatbed Options</h3>
    <p>
    Specify what kind of bed you want - MK52 or a plain ol' rectangle.
    </p>
    <div class="control-group" title="Heatbed Style">
        <label class="control-label" for="settings-webcamStreamRatio">matplotlib_heatmap_background_image_style</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <select data-bind="options: matplotlib_heatmap_background_image_style, value: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.PrusaMeshMap.matplotlib_heatmap_background_image_style"></select>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Output Options</h3>
    <p>
    Specify the appearence of the graph. You can use Bicubic or a "topology" map called contourf
    </p>
    <div class="control-group" title="output_mode">
        <label class="control-label" for="Map Style">output_mode</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <select data-bind="options: output_mode, value: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.PrusaMeshMap.output_mode"></select>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

    <h3>Testing mode</h3>
    <p>
    Enable Testing Mode for debugging. Or turn it off. :D
    </p>
    <div class="control-group" title="testing mode">
        <label class="control-label" for="testing mode">pluginTestingMode</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <select data-bind="options: pluginTestingMode, value: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.PrusaMeshMap.pluginTestingMode"></select>
        </div>
    </div>    

    <h3>Heatmap Options</h3>
    <div class="control-group" title="Color Scheme">
        <label class="control-label" for="settings-webcamStreamRatio">Colormap</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <select data-bind="options: matplotlib_heatmap_theme_options, value: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.PrusaMeshMap.matplotlib_heatmap_theme"></select>
            <span class="help-inline">See <a href="https://matplotlib.org/examples/color/colormaps_reference.html" target="matplotlib-colors">colormap reference</a> for previews.</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</form>
